                            <comment id="12611678" author="pi_song" created="Tue, 8 Jul 2008 16:20:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems to be OK except when you use DESC keyword.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unit tests attached.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12612282" author="alangates" created="Wed, 9 Jul 2008 21:19:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch contains a lot. The relevant areas are:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) Fixed DataByteArray.compareTo to first check byte to byte and only size when the bytes compare equal, instead of other way around (that is, it now matches String.compareTo behavior).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) Fixed use of binary comparator for hadoop sorting. It was being used anytime we were sorting on a tuple. It should instead be used anytime we are not doing an order by.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
